### Phase 3 - Registration Flow API Tests
### Use REST Client extension in VS Code or import to Postman/Thunder Client

@baseUrl = http://localhost:3001/api/v1/auth
@email = test@example.com
@name = John Doe
@username = johndoe
@password = Test123!@#
@code = 123456

### 1. Health Check
GET http://localhost:3001/health

### 2. Request Email Verification
POST {{baseUrl}}/request-verification
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "{{email}}"
}

### 3. Verify Email (use code from email or console logs)
POST {{baseUrl}}/verify-email
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "{{email}}",
  "code": "{{code}}"
}

### 4. Register User
POST {{baseUrl}}/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "{{email}}",
  "name": "{{name}}",
  "username": "{{username}}",
  "password": "{{password}}",
  "passwordConfirm": "{{password}}"
}

### 5. Login
POST {{baseUrl}}/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "{{email}}",
  "password": "{{password}}"
}

### 6. Get Current User (use token from login/register response)
GET {{baseUrl}}/me
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_ACCESS_TOKEN_HERE

### 7. Refresh Token
POST {{baseUrl}}/refresh
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "refreshToken": "YOUR_REFRESH_TOKEN_HERE"
}

